\section{Agnolotti}
These shell-like ravioli from Piedmont, northern italy, are fashioned
from small pieces of flattened dough made of wheat flour and egg, and
are often filled with braised veal, port, vegetables or cheese. The
true agnolotto should feature a crinkled edge, cut using a fluted
pasta wheel. Recommended with melted butter and sage

